president obama's interfaith and community service campus challenge workshop events at stanford president obama's interfaith and community service campus challenge workshop facebook twitter email print add to calendar president obama's interfaith and community service campus challenge is a call to colleges and universities to commit to a year of interfaith cooperation and community service programming on campus stanford's theme is hospitality and welcoming the stranger immigration in the bay area through the lens of hunger and homelessness there's still time to join the challenge attend this workshop to learn about community service partners and get instructions on developing a service plan when sunday december 4 2011 5 00 pm approximate duration of 1.5 hour s where haas center map audience students tags other public service sponsor hillel at stanford office for religious life haas center for public service contact 723 1762 religious life stanford edu permalink http events stanford edu events 299 29999 more info last modified november 22 2011
